quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"SAY: \"O disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not serve what you serve
  109,3,nor are you serving what I serve
  109,4,I will not worship what you have worshipped
  109,5,neither will you worship what I worship
  109,6,You have your religion while I have my religion
  110,1,When God´s support comes as well as victory
  110,2,and you see mankind entering God´s religion in droves
  110,3,"then hymn your Lord´s praise and beg Him for forgiveness, since He is so Relenting"
  111,1,"May Abo-Lahab´s both hands waste away and may he waste away [as well]"
  111,2,His wealth and what he´s earned will never profit him
  111,3,he´ll roast in a fire with a flame
  111,4,while his wife who carries kindling around
  111,5,will have a palm-fiber rope around her neck